Members of the Rivers State National Assembly caucus on Friday hailed Justice Mary Odili of the Supreme Court as she clocks 69. They described her as a bridge builder across boundaries. In a joint statement issued and signed by both legislative Chambers caucus leaders, Senator George Sekibo and Rep Kingsley Chinda, said: “Wife of our leader Peter Odilli, our dear mother and Nation builder: A virtous woman of inestimable value. “We pray that God Almighty increase you and keep you in sound health, strength, wisdom and vigour.”